V. Case Study: Geospatial Redirection (Santa Ana Incident)

During a high-tension encounter at the observatory in Santa Ana, CA, the DLNTP was utilized to neutralize a "Social Injection Attack."

The Query: A suspicious local actor attempted to verify the HVA’s location ("Where are you staying?").

The Response: The operator utilized a planed Phonetic Misdirection, stating "Santa Clara" (a location 350 miles away).

The Validation: The HVA (The Artist) acted as a Synchronized Node, nodding to the false data.

The Capture: While the threat was "Null-Routed" by the false location, a team member (The Flank) extracted a Primary Key (Phone Number) for further reverse-recon.
